import React from 'react';
import { Box, Container, Typography, Grid } from '@mui/material';
import './home.css';

const Home = () => {
  return (
    <Container className="home-container">
      <Box textAlign="center" my={4} className="intro">
        <Box className="intro-container">
          <Typography variant="h2" component="h1" gutterBottom className="title">
            Welcome to Our Organization
          </Typography>
          <Typography
            variant="h5"
            gutterBottom
            className="subtitle"
            display="flex"
            alignItems="center"
            justifyContent="center"
          >
            Empowering Communities, Enabling Change
          </Typography>
          <Typography variant="body1" paragraph className="description">
            Our organization is committed to making a positive impact on society by addressing
            pressing issues and providing innovative solutions. We work with communities to
            foster growth, resilience, and sustainable development.
          </Typography>
        </Box>
      </Box>
      <Box my={4}>
        <Typography variant="h4" component="h2" gutterBottom className="section-title">
          Our Initiatives
        </Typography>
        <Grid container spacing={4} justifyContent="center">
          {/* Placeholder for Images */}
          {[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6].map((placeholder, index) => (
            <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={4} key={index}>
              <Box className="image-placeholder">
                <Typography variant="h6" className="image-description">
                  Initiative {placeholder}
                </Typography>
              </Box>
            </Grid>
          ))}
        </Grid>
      </Box>
    </Container>
  );
};

export default Home;
